T-Pot Attack Map
The T-Pot Attack Map is a fascinating and interactive dashboard. As the name suggests, this dashboard shows you exactly who is attacking your T-Pot instance. 
It displays detailed information such as:

Country of Origin
IP Address
Specific Honeypot Being Targeted
Type of Service Under Attack

Each attack is color-coded, making it easy to identify which service the attacker is using at a glance.

Additionally, the Attack Map provides real-time updates, allowing you to monitor ongoing attacks as they happen. 
This visualization helps in understanding the geographical distribution of attacks and identifying patterns in the types of services being targeted. 
The dashboard also offers filtering options, enabling you to focus on specific honeypots, services, or regions for more detailed analysis.

By leveraging the insights from the Attack Map, you can better understand the threat landscape and enhance your defensive strategies.
